01:00:56,195 --> 01:00:58,571
You look at me
like I'm doing something wrong,

542
01:00:58,656 --> 01:01:01,574
like I did something wrong,
I don't understand it.

543
01:01:03,577 --> 01:01:05,703
I don't know anything.

544
01:01:05,788 --> 01:01:08,081
- DETECTIVE 1: Your name?
- BABE: I told you my name!

545
01:01:08,165 --> 01:01:10,583
- DETECTIVE 1: Take it easy.
- Thomas Babington Levy.

546
01:01:10,668 --> 01:01:11,668
DETECTIVE 1: You're a student.

547
01:01:11,752 --> 01:01:15,421
I come from a family of historians.
My card is proof.

548
01:01:17,424 --> 01:01:21,886
Please put the papers down.
Tell them. Put the papers down!

549
01:01:21,971 --> 01:01:24,430
DETECTIVE 1: Take it easy.
What's in the papers?

550
01:01:24,765 --> 01:01:27,350
It's a paper I'm writing.

551
01:01:27,434 --> 01:01:29,227
DETECTIVE 2: Would you
tell me who this is?

552
01:01:29,311 --> 01:01:30,353
It's my father.

553
01:01:30,437 --> 01:01:31,938
DETECTIVE 1:
Where can we contact him?

554
01:01:33,941 --> 01:01:35,650
He's not alive any more.

555
01:01:36,151 --> 01:01:40,196
- DETECTIVE 2: Is this yours?
- Yes. The license is in the drawer.

556
01:01:40,281 --> 01:01:41,364
I don't know anything.

557
01:01:41,448 --> 01:01:45,201
Why ask about this?
It has nothing to do with it.

558
01:01:46,120 --> 01:01:48,121
DETECTIVE 1: Okay, enough.

559
01:01:49,540 --> 01:01:51,916
- Here.
- Thanks.

560
01:01:53,878 --> 01:01:57,380
DETECTIVE 1: I know this wasn't easy
and this is a bad time for you,

561
01:01:57,464 --> 01:02:01,134
but it's gotta be done,
you can understand that, right?

562
01:02:04,013 --> 01:02:05,513
Good evening, sir.

563
01:02:35,753 --> 01:02:39,047
- Whoever did it must have set him up.
- Get them all out of here.

564
01:02:39,131 --> 01:02:41,049
I'll get the ambulance guys.

565
01:02:42,885 --> 01:02:44,177
(DOOR CLOSES)

566
01:02:48,015 --> 01:02:51,684
I'm sorry to intrude.
I was a friend of your brother's.

567
01:02:52,269 --> 01:02:56,522
My name is Peter Janeway.
Call me Janey. All my friends do.

568
01:02:56,774 --> 01:02:58,775
I'm not your friend.

569
01:03:00,527 --> 01:03:01,819
Listen.

570
01:03:02,988 --> 01:03:07,492
- I'm anxious as you to find who did this.
- I'm a little more anxious.

571
01:03:09,036 --> 01:03:12,664
- I think it may have been political.
- Political? Why?

572
01:03:12,790 --> 01:03:16,209
Considering what your brother did.
And your father, of course.

573
01:03:16,752 --> 01:03:20,296
- What about my father?
- He was H.V. Levy, for Christ sakes.

574
01:03:20,381 --> 01:03:23,174
He's been dead for 20 years,
and he was innocent.

575
01:03:23,258 --> 01:03:24,968
What are you saying?

576
01:03:25,386 --> 01:03:28,888
Get off my back!
They've been after me for two hours!

577
01:03:29,098 --> 01:03:30,431
I didn't mean to imply...

578
01:03:30,516 --> 01:03:33,559
They told me they were done!
What are you saying?

579
01:03:34,853 --> 01:03:36,229
I'm sorry.

580
01:03:38,065 --> 01:03:39,107
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

581
01:03:39,191 --> 01:03:40,566
Come in.

582
01:04:22,609 --> 01:04:23,818
Listen...

583
01:04:24,737 --> 01:04:28,031
Why don't we begin
with what happened tonight, hmm?

584
01:04:32,369 --> 01:04:36,372
Perhaps you could
give me some of the details.

585
01:04:37,416 --> 01:04:41,502
I was here. Doc died. You came.

586
01:04:42,963 --> 01:04:44,213
That's it?

587
01:04:45,382 --> 01:04:47,341
I'm a demon for details.

588
01:04:50,554 --> 01:04:54,182
- You want me to explain, then?
- That's right.

589
01:04:54,266 --> 01:04:56,392
- Where did your brother live?
- In Washington.

590
01:04:56,477 --> 01:04:59,604
- What did he do?
- Oil business.

591
01:05:00,230 --> 01:05:01,898
Wrong.

592
01:05:01,982 --> 01:05:04,525
I know exactly how Doc made his living.

593
01:05:04,610 --> 01:05:08,988
The closest he got to the oil business
was when he filled up with gas.

594
01:05:09,114 --> 01:05:13,117
- Tell me what you're talking about.
- All right. Follow me.

595
01:05:13,786 --> 01:05:16,954
Doc lived in Washington,
which is the centre of...

596
01:05:17,039 --> 01:05:18,790
- Government.
- Correct.

597
01:05:18,999 --> 01:05:21,125
All the branches are competitive.

598
01:05:21,460 --> 01:05:24,045
Truth is they're all paranoid schmucks.

599
01:05:24,880 --> 01:05:28,883
When the gap gets too large between
what the FBI can handle effectively

600
01:05:28,967 --> 01:05:33,137
and what the CIA
doesn't wanna deal with, we step in.

601
01:05:33,222 --> 01:05:35,848
- Who's we?
- The Division.

602
01:05:36,809 --> 01:05:39,769
- And my brother worked with you?
- Yes.

603
01:05:39,853 --> 01:05:41,646
You're full of shit.

604
01:05:48,195 --> 01:05:51,072
- What do you do exactly?
- We provide.

605
01:05:51,698 --> 01:05:54,408
- Provide what?
- Anything.

606
01:05:56,495 --> 01:05:58,454
And you two work together?

607
01:05:58,622 --> 01:06:01,666
Why didn't Doc tell me?
Why did he lie to me?

608
01:06:02,292 --> 01:06:05,503
He was afraid you'd be
disappointed in him, I expect.

609
01:06:07,464 --> 01:06:10,716
We were very close for many years.
Believe me.

610
01:06:11,510 --> 01:06:13,719
I know whereof I speak.

611
01:06:18,267 --> 01:06:22,228
Doc was desperate to get here.
Remember anything he said?

612
01:06:22,855 --> 01:06:27,400
He said my name a couple of times.

613
01:06:30,237 --> 01:06:32,613
Okay, I'm just guessing now,

614
01:06:33,448 --> 01:06:36,909
but whoever killed him
will probably want to speak to you.

615
01:06:37,578 --> 01:06:41,622
- I don't know anything.
- They won't know till they talk with you.

616
01:06:42,040 --> 01:06:45,084
I'm staying across the park,
at The Carlyle,

617
01:06:45,836 --> 01:06:49,088
and if you don't mind,
I'd like to use you as bait.

618
01:06:51,008 --> 01:06:52,967
- Bait.
- Yes.

619
01:06:54,094 --> 01:06:56,512
- Will they come tonight?
- No.

620
01:06:57,514 --> 01:07:02,268
I know it's risky, and I don't wanna
force you to do it. It's up to you.

621
01:07:46,313 --> 01:07:47,313
(SIGHS)

622
01:08:59,469 --> 01:09:00,469
(CREAKING)

623
01:09:03,890 --> 01:09:05,224
MAN 1: Tub.

624
01:09:06,560 --> 01:09:08,227
MAN 2: All right.

625
01:09:14,985 --> 01:09:16,110
(CREAKING)

626
01:09:16,778 --> 01:09:20,364
MAN: (WHISPERING)
All right, I got it. Here it is.

627
01:09:25,329 --> 01:09:27,121
Turn it off. All right.

628
01:09:31,376 --> 01:09:33,085
Shit. Jesus!

629
01:09:47,809 --> 01:09:49,101
Shit.

630
01:10:11,291 --> 01:10:12,792
(WOOD CRACKING)

631
01:10:46,368 --> 01:10:47,660
BABE: Help!

632
01:10:56,044 --> 01:10:59,255
Help! Help! Please!

633
01:10:59,881 --> 01:11:02,174
Somebody help me!

634
01:11:05,011 --> 01:11:07,263
Help!

635
01:11:10,392 --> 01:11:12,435
Help!

636
01:11:15,981 --> 01:11:18,691
Help! Help!

637
01:11:37,627 --> 01:11:38,627
(GASPING)

638
01:12:58,750 --> 01:13:00,084
Is it safe?

639
01:13:15,016 --> 01:13:16,559
Is it safe?

640
01:13:18,228 --> 01:13:19,645
Are you talking to me?

641
01:13:19,896 --> 01:13:22,398
- Is it safe?
- Is what safe?

642
01:13:24,401 --> 01:13:27,069
- Is it safe?
- I don't know what you mean.

643
01:13:27,946 --> 01:13:31,323
I can't tell you
if something is safe or not

644
01:13:32,117 --> 01:13:35,160
unless I know specifically
what you're talking about.

645
01:13:40,667 --> 01:13:42,209
Is it safe?

646
01:13:44,337 --> 01:13:46,213
Tell me what the "it" refers to.

647
01:13:48,800 --> 01:13:50,384
Is it safe?

648
01:13:51,595 --> 01:13:54,847
Yes, it's safe. It's very safe.
So safe you wouldn't believe it.

649
01:13:57,392 --> 01:13:59,101
Is it safe?

650
01:14:02,689 --> 01:14:06,775
No, it's not safe.
It's very dangerous. Be careful.

651
01:14:34,679 --> 01:14:36,555
Relax, relax.

652
01:14:36,723 --> 01:14:40,517
Come on. Open. Open. It's okay.

653
01:14:53,365 --> 01:14:57,076
- That hurt? I should think it would.
- Uh-huh.

654
01:14:57,243 --> 01:14:59,161
You should take better care
of your teeth.

655
01:14:59,245 --> 01:15:02,081
You have quite a cavity here.

656
01:15:03,583 --> 01:15:06,418
- Is it safe?
- I told you I can't tell you... (SCREAMS)

657
01:15:12,592 --> 01:15:16,303
- Think he knows?
- Of course. He's being very stubborn.

658
01:15:19,474 --> 01:15:21,725
No, please. Please don't. No.

659
01:15:23,478 --> 01:15:25,396
SZELL: It's okay.

660
01:15:30,485 --> 01:15:32,569
Is it not remarkable?

661
01:15:32,654 --> 01:15:37,116
Simple oil of cloves
and how amazing the results.

662
01:15:37,409 --> 01:15:42,204
Life can be that simple.
Relief, discomfort.

663
01:15:42,789 --> 01:15:47,376
Now, which of these I next apply,
that decision is in your hands,

664
01:15:49,129 --> 01:15:53,132
so take your time and tell me.

665
01:15:54,384 --> 01:15:57,428
- Is it safe?
- Please...

666
01:15:59,222 --> 01:16:00,472
Please stop.

667
01:16:07,939 --> 01:16:10,482
- MAN 1: Take him.
- MAN 2: I got him.

668
01:17:00,366 --> 01:17:01,658
More.

669
01:17:05,121 --> 01:17:06,538
Thank you.

670
01:17:11,503 --> 01:17:12,711
More.

671
01:17:21,179 --> 01:17:22,179
(GROANS)

672
01:17:30,897 --> 01:17:32,064
(YELLING)

673
01:17:50,542 --> 01:17:52,584
Thank you. Thank you.

674
01:17:58,925 --> 01:18:02,845
Things are coming together.
Down, or your head gets blown off.

675
01:18:03,054 --> 01:18:06,014
Those two guys I wasted
work for Christian Szell.

676
01:18:06,099 --> 01:18:07,724
- Know that name?
- No.

677
01:18:07,809 --> 01:18:10,018
He did experiments at Auschwitz.

678
01:18:10,103 --> 01:18:15,107
He was called The White Angel,
Der Weiﬂe Engel, due to his white hair.

679
01:18:15,191 --> 01:18:17,693
The wealthiest and most wanted Nazi
left alive.

680
01:18:17,777 --> 01:18:19,903
He's hiding out in Uruguay.

681
01:18:21,781 --> 01:18:27,369
In '45, Szell told Jews in Auschwitz
he'd help them escape for a price.

682
01:18:27,453 --> 01:18:30,956
He started out with gold, naturally,
but went on to diamonds.

683
01:18:31,040 --> 01:18:32,791
Heard this?

684
01:18:32,876 --> 01:18:34,251
Szell saw the end early.

685
01:18:34,335 --> 01:18:36,461
His brother took
the diamonds to America

686
01:18:36,546 --> 01:18:38,881
to a safe deposit box in New York.

687
01:18:38,965 --> 01:18:40,132
Szell's brother had the key.

688
01:18:40,216 --> 01:18:42,801
The only other key
Szell kept in Uruguay.

689
01:18:42,886 --> 01:18:46,847
If he comes out to use it,
he'll expose himself to great risk.

690
01:18:46,931 --> 01:18:50,851
Everything went fine till his brother
got killed by an oil truck.

691
01:18:51,144 --> 01:18:53,854
Why was it natural to start with gold?

692
01:18:53,980 --> 01:18:56,732
He took it from the Jews' teeth
before he burned them.

693
01:18:56,816 --> 01:18:58,317
Szell was a dentist.

694
01:19:01,613 --> 01:19:06,033
He's not coming to America,
Mr Janeway. He's here.

695
01:19:06,117 --> 01:19:07,993
No. We'd have known it.

696
01:19:08,077 --> 01:19:11,246
The dentist almost killed me.
He kept saying, "Is it safe?"

697
01:19:11,331 --> 01:19:14,625
White hair? Keep your head down!
Did he have white hair?

698
01:19:14,709 --> 01:19:16,293
He was bald.

699
01:19:16,628 --> 01:19:20,005
He's shaved his head!
He's here, and he's panicked.

700
01:19:20,089 --> 01:19:24,092
- Why is he after me?
- Your brother was a diamond courier.

701
01:19:24,177 --> 01:19:27,387
Szell thinks Doc said something to you
before he died.

702
01:19:27,472 --> 01:19:30,891
- Did he?
- You say my brother worked for Szell?

703
01:19:30,975 --> 01:19:34,561
No! He worked for us.
Everything we do cuts both ways.

704
01:19:35,104 --> 01:19:38,899
Szell ratted on all his buddies.
He kept track on all the Nazis.

705
01:19:38,983 --> 01:19:41,485
When we wanted to bring one in,
we went to Szell.

706
01:19:41,569 --> 01:19:44,446
Babe, you gotta do one thing for me,
just one thing.

707
01:19:44,530 --> 01:19:47,074
- Quit protecting Doc!
- I'm not.

708
01:19:47,158 --> 01:19:50,702
- He kept alive to say something.
- He didn't.

709
01:19:50,787 --> 01:19:53,288
- He must have. Tell me!
- Nothing!

710
01:19:53,373 --> 01:19:54,957
Shit!

711
01:20:03,091 --> 01:20:06,426
I thought you killed them.
You killed them!

712
01:20:06,719 --> 01:20:08,470
You killed them!

713
01:20:09,889 --> 01:20:11,682
You killed them!

714
01:20:12,058 --> 01:20:14,017
You fucking killed them!

715
01:20:14,435 --> 01:20:16,436
You killed my brother!

716
01:20:23,736 --> 01:20:26,738
I don't think he knows anything.
I think he knows too much.

717
01:20:26,823 --> 01:20:29,783
You can afford to think what you wish.
I can't.

718
01:20:41,754 --> 01:20:45,424
The gun had blanks,
the knife a retractable blade.

719
01:20:45,508 --> 01:20:49,720
Hardly original, but effective enough.
I think you'll agree.

720
01:20:49,846 --> 01:20:51,680
(WATER RUNNING)

721
01:20:51,764 --> 01:20:55,434
I'm told you are a graduate student.

722
01:20:55,685 --> 01:20:57,269
Brilliant, yeah?

723
01:20:58,771 --> 01:21:02,733
You're an historian,
and I am part of history.

724
01:21:02,817 --> 01:21:06,695
I should have thought
you would have found me interesting.

725
01:21:06,779 --> 01:21:10,490
Frankly, I am disappointed
in your silence.

726
01:21:10,575 --> 01:21:13,035
Why do you have so little accent?

727
01:21:13,119 --> 01:21:17,122
I had alexia as a child.
Alexia is a disease...

728
01:21:17,206 --> 01:21:19,916
I know, it's where
you can't understand written speech.

729
01:21:20,001 --> 01:21:21,209
Highest marks.

730
01:21:21,294 --> 01:21:27,132
At any event, my writing is childish still,
but I'm a fanatic about spoken language.

731
01:21:28,301 --> 01:21:31,553
I envy you your school days. Enjoy them.

732
01:21:31,637 --> 01:21:35,432
It's the last time in your life
no one expects anything of you.

733
01:21:36,225 --> 01:21:41,313
I know I behaved terribly,
but I had to be sure what you knew.

734
01:21:41,397 --> 01:21:42,564
You see...

735
01:21:42,982 --> 01:21:46,068
I'm positive
your brother meant to rob me

736
01:21:46,152 --> 01:21:49,821
when I left the bank with my diamonds.

737
01:21:49,906 --> 01:21:51,907
I don't know anything.

738
01:21:51,991 --> 01:21:56,161
- Did Scylla plan the robbery alone?
- Robbery?

739
01:21:59,791 --> 01:22:03,126
- You know the value of diamonds?
- No, I don't.

