- (TYRES SREECHING)

986
01:50:13,232 --> 01:50:14,232
(HONKING)

987
01:50:16,152 --> 01:50:17,736
(PEOPLE CLAMOURING)

988
01:50:22,450 --> 01:50:24,242
Szell!

989
01:50:41,636 --> 01:50:46,306
I know who you are, you murderer.
I know who you are!

990
01:50:46,390 --> 01:50:49,226
Help! Help!

991
01:50:49,811 --> 01:50:54,481
The man needs help here!
Help! Quick! A doctor! Quick!

992
01:50:57,235 --> 01:50:59,402
58th Street and Madison.

993
01:51:27,640 --> 01:51:28,557
(DOOR BUZZING)

994
01:51:29,433 --> 01:51:31,977
- Morning, sir. Thank you.
- Thank you.

995
01:51:37,942 --> 01:51:41,570
GUARD: Two-five-nine-six-six.

996
01:52:06,137 --> 01:52:08,346
All finished, Henry. Thank you.

997
01:52:08,431 --> 01:52:11,683
- Everything all right, Mrs Rosenheim?
- Yes. See you next week.

998
01:52:11,976 --> 01:52:13,852
There you are, sir.

999
01:52:15,104 --> 01:52:18,106
Close the door for the light, sir.
No one can enter.

1000
01:52:45,217 --> 01:52:46,217
Ha!

1001
01:52:55,353 --> 01:52:57,479
Everything all right, sir?

1002
01:52:59,732 --> 01:53:01,274
Yeah!

1003
01:53:04,070 --> 01:53:05,695
Yes!

1004
01:53:44,443 --> 01:53:46,236
BABE: It isn't safe.

1005
01:53:49,240 --> 01:53:50,532
Move.

1006
01:53:51,909 --> 01:53:53,910
They're all dead. Move.

1007
01:53:56,038 --> 01:53:59,124
SZELL: You'd be foolish
to do anything hasty.

1008
01:53:59,208 --> 01:54:00,500
BABE: Move.

1009
01:54:00,584 --> 01:54:02,293
SZELL: I have things in my possession...

1010
01:54:02,378 --> 01:54:03,586
BABE: Just keep moving.

1011
01:54:18,185 --> 01:54:24,024
DISPATCHER: Name is Arnie, walks
with a limp, green jacket, brown pants.

1012
01:54:24,150 --> 01:54:25,608
Ten-four.

1013
01:54:53,929 --> 01:54:57,932
- What are you guys doing in here?
- BABE: We'll just be a little while.

1014
01:54:58,017 --> 01:55:00,977
- There's nobody allowed in here.
- Well, get out!

1015
01:55:01,479 --> 01:55:02,771
Get out!

1016
01:55:04,315 --> 01:55:05,523
Hurry up!

1017
01:55:06,400 --> 01:55:09,069
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

1018
01:55:09,153 --> 01:55:11,404
Okay, let's see what you got.

1019
01:55:13,991 --> 01:55:16,910
If you will just give me a chance
to get this open.

1020
01:55:16,994 --> 01:55:18,912
That's okay. Take your time.

1021
01:55:32,051 --> 01:55:35,678
All this happened because you were
afraid you were gonna be robbed?

1022
01:55:37,098 --> 01:55:38,389
Yes.

1023
01:55:38,933 --> 01:55:40,850
But you weren't sure.

1024
01:55:41,477 --> 01:55:42,769
No.

1025
01:55:45,231 --> 01:55:46,898
Jesus Christ.

1026
01:55:47,650 --> 01:55:51,528
I was in a state of hysteria, you know.

1027
01:55:57,243 --> 01:56:00,370
Don't you want to
take a closer look than that?

1028
01:56:02,790 --> 01:56:04,916
- No.
- You see...

1029
01:56:06,710 --> 01:56:10,088
In a sense, one becomes
more emotional with age.

1030
01:56:10,172 --> 01:56:14,843
First after a lifetime of being taken
by friends and enemies alike,

1031
01:56:14,927 --> 01:56:18,429
and then, just when you think
you have your possession sure,

1032
01:56:18,514 --> 01:56:21,099
your health begins to go.

1033
01:56:22,476 --> 01:56:27,772
- That is, of course, the ultimate theft.
- That's close enough.

1034
01:56:27,857 --> 01:56:31,568
- In the circumstances, one's paranoia...
- Close enough!

1035
01:56:31,652 --> 01:56:33,862
- ...gets out of hand.
- Stop!

1036
01:56:42,746 --> 01:56:43,830
Well?

1037
01:56:45,249 --> 01:56:47,750
What are you going to do now,
shoot me?

1038
01:56:49,128 --> 01:56:51,004
No, I don't think so.

1039
01:56:51,088 --> 01:56:55,175
Then you'll take these from me.
If I could say a word about that?

1040
01:56:56,635 --> 01:56:58,136
No, you can keep them.

1041
01:57:01,807 --> 01:57:04,893
You can keep
as many as you can swallow.

1042
01:57:05,603 --> 01:57:08,188
Pardon me,
I'm not quite sure what you said.

1043
01:57:08,272 --> 01:57:09,606
Swallow?

1044
01:57:09,815 --> 01:57:11,441
Yeah, swallow.

1045
01:57:12,443 --> 01:57:13,693
Eat.

1046
01:57:15,279 --> 01:57:16,446
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1047
01:57:18,949 --> 01:57:21,951
- You're joking.
- No, I don't think so.

1048
01:57:33,964 --> 01:57:35,215
I'm not joking.

1049
01:57:36,800 --> 01:57:38,134
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1050
01:57:41,263 --> 01:57:42,263
(YELLS)

1051
01:57:42,723 --> 01:57:44,515
No, wait!

1052
01:57:45,809 --> 01:57:48,561
That man who was here
has seen your gun!

1053
01:57:48,646 --> 01:57:50,396
He'll bring others!

1054
01:57:52,650 --> 01:57:53,983
Swallow!

1055
01:57:55,611 --> 01:57:57,528
This is madness!

1056
01:58:10,292 --> 01:58:11,584
Swallow.

1057
01:59:07,766 --> 01:59:09,225
Again.

1058
01:59:22,031 --> 01:59:23,156
No.

1059
01:59:24,533 --> 01:59:25,742
I won't.

1060
01:59:27,411 --> 01:59:29,245
You'll have to shoot me.

1061
01:59:32,541 --> 01:59:34,250
Come on.

1062
01:59:34,335 --> 01:59:35,626
Shoot.

1063
01:59:41,383 --> 01:59:42,759
You won't.

1064
01:59:45,471 --> 01:59:46,888
You can't.

1065
01:59:48,932 --> 01:59:50,641
You're too weak.

1066
01:59:52,353 --> 01:59:57,357
Your father was weak in his way,
your brother in his, now you in yours.

1067
01:59:58,901 --> 02:00:02,945
You are all so predictable.

1068
02:00:26,095 --> 02:00:27,220
(YELLING)

1069
02:00:32,184 --> 02:00:33,935
Go get them!

1070
02:00:37,272 --> 02:00:38,481
(GRUNTING)

1071
02:00:45,155 --> 02:00:46,447
(GROANS)